Paper: hep-th/9905021

Date: 1999-05-04

Title: On Generations

Authors: A. Rivero (U. of Zaragoza)

Comments: 5 pages, LaTeX, small additions

The well known operator ordering ambiguity could motivate the existence ofgenerations. This possibility is explored by exploiting the relationshipbetween ordering and discretization rules. Context is drawn from lattice theoryand non commutative geometry.